{"title_page": "Jack Harlow", "text_new": "{{short description|American rapper}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Jack Harlow\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Jackman Thomas Harlow<ref>[https://repertoire.bmi.com/Catalog.aspx?detail=writerid&page=1&fromrow=1&torow=25&keyid=1977162&subid=0] {{dead link|date=April 2020}}</ref>\n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1998|03|13}}\n| birth_place      = [[Louisville]], [[Kentucky]], U.S.\n| origin           = \n| genre            = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Rapper|songwriter}}\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| years_active     = 2015\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|Generation Now|[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|Private Garden|[[Cyhi the Prynce]]|[[Don Cannon]]|[[Bryson Tiller]]|[[DJ Drama]]|2forwOyNE|Shloob|Ace Pro|Ronnie Lucciano|Quiiso}}\n| website          = {{URL|jackharlow.us/}}\n}}\n\n'''Jackman Thomas \"Jack\" Harlow''' (born March 13, 1998)<ref name=\"LouisMain\">{{cite news | last=Moss| first=Josh| title =Kid with a Mic| work =Louisville| date =4 August 2017 | url =https://www.louisville.com/content/kid-mic| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> is an American rapper and songwriter.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/02/05/jack-harlow-stays-true-to-his-roots|title=Jack Harlow Stays True to His Roots|work=The Fader|date=February 5, 2019|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref> He is signed to Generation Now and [[Atlantic Records]]. He is also the co-founder of his own musical collective, Private Garden. He is best known for his single \"Whats Poppin\", which peaked at number 36 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8550188/emerging-artists-chart-debuts-jack-harlow-andy-shauf |title=Jack Harlow, Andy Shauf and Jeff Parker Debut on Emerging Artists Chart |website=Billboard.com |date=2020-02-05 |accessdate=2020-04-10}}</ref> Jack Harlow first started  rising to mainstream popularity due to his affiliations with rapper Lil Uzi Vert\n\n==Early life==\nHarlow was born and raised in [[Louisville, Kentucky]].<ref name=\"XXLBreak\">{{cite news | last=Krastz| first=Roger| title =The Break Presents: Jack Harlow| publisher =XXL| date =12 January 2018 | url =http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2018/01/jack-harlow-interview-the-break/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"LouisMain\"/><ref name=\"BBOct\">{{cite news | last=Elibert| first=Mark| title =Jack Harlow Talks 'Loose' Mixtape, Putting Louisville on the Map & Working With DJ Drama, Don Cannon| publisher =Billboard| date =10 October 2018 | url =https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8478971/jack-harlow-loose-mixtape-dj-drama-interview| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> Harlow began rapping at age 12. He and a friend used a ''[[Guitar Hero]]'' microphone and a laptop to record rhymes and songs. They made a [[Compact disc|CD]] entitled ''Rippin' and Rappin{{'}}'' and sold copies at their school ([[Highland Middle School (Louisville, Kentucky)|Highland Middle School]]). When he was in seventh grade, Harlow acquired a professional microphone and made his first mixtape, ''Extra Credit'', using the moniker \"Mr. Harlow\".<ref name=\"LouisMain\"/>\n\nHarlow attended [[Atherton High School]], graduating in 2016. During his freshman year, his [[YouTube]] videos drew the attention of major labels, but he chose not to pursue any of the deals offered to him at the time. In November 2014 during his junior year, he released another mixtape, ''Finally Handsome''.<ref name=\"LouisMain\"/><ref name=\"DJBFinally\">{{cite news | last=| first=| title =Jack Harlow - Finally Handsome | publisher=DJ Booth| date =7 November 2014 | url =https://djbooth.net/index/albums/review/jack-harlow-finally-handsome| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150117025429/https://djbooth.net/index/albums/review/jack-harlow-finally-handsome| archive-date=17 January 2015| url-status=dead| access-date =13 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn November 2015, Harlow released his first commercial album, an [[Extended play|EP]] entitled ''The Handsome Harlow''. It was released through [[Gill Holland]]'s sonaBLAST! record label.<ref name=\"LouisMain\"/><ref name=\"Louis2\">{{cite news | last=Messmer| first=Alexis| title =Jack Harlow Talks His First Commercial Release and What's Next | publisher =Louisville| date =18 December 2015 | url =https://www.louisville.com/content/jack-harlow-talks-his-first-commercial-release-and-whats-next| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> Throughout high school, he often played sold out shows at Louisville venues like the [[Mercury Ballroom]], Headliners, and the Haymarket Whiskey Bar.<ref name=\"LouisMain\"/><ref name=\"XXLBreak\"/> In early 2016, he released a single, \"Never Woulda Known\", which featured Johnny Spanish and was produced by Syk Sense. In March of that year, he opened for [[Vince Staples]] in Louisville.<ref name=\"CJ\">{{cite news | last=Puckett| first=Jeffrey Lee| title =Rapper Jack Harlow is on it like MacGyver| newspaper =The Courier-Journal| date =8 March 2016 | url =https://www.courier-journal.com/story/entertainment/music/2016/03/08/jack-harlow-louisville-rapper/81228018/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2016 less than a month after graduating high school, he released the mixtape, ''18'', which was the first album on his label and music collective, Private Garden.<ref name=\"EMIntro\">{{cite news | last=Luisa| first=Paige| title =Introducing: Jack Harlow| publisher =Ear Milk| date =18 July 2016 | url =https://earmilk.com/2016/07/18/introducing-jack-harlow/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"LEO18\">{{cite news | last=Bishop| first=Syd| title =Into the wild: A conversation with Jack Harlow| newspaper =Louisville Eccentric Observer| date =15 June 2016 | url =https://www.leoweekly.com/2016/06/wild-conversation-jack-harlow/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> The collective also features Harlow's frequent collaborators, the Homies, composed of Louisville rappers and producers Ace Pro, 2forwOyNE, Shloob, Quiiso, and Ronnie Lucciano.<ref name=\"LouisMain\"/> Over the course of the next year, Harlow performed at [[South by Southwest]], [[Bonnaroo Music Festival|Bonnaroo]], and the [[Forecastle Festival]]. He also spent time traveling back and forth between Louisville and [[Atlanta]] to work with engineer/mixer, KY Engineering. In March 2017, he released the song \"Hitchcock\", produced by 2forwOyNE and J-Reid.<ref name=\"LouisMain\"/><ref name=\"Weiss\">{{cite news | last=Poe| first=Allen| title =North By Northwest: On Jack Harlow's \"Hitchcock\"| publisher =Passion of the Weiss| date =13 March 2017 | url =https://www.passionweiss.com/2017/03/13/jack-harlow-hitchcock/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn the summer of 2017, he released the single \"Routine\".<ref name=\"LouisMain\"/> In October of that year, he released another single, \"Dark Knight\", with an accompanying music video. He credits [[Cyhi the Prynce|CyHi the Prynce]] with helping him work through his [[writer's block]] and finish the song.<ref name=\"MA\">{{cite news | last=Lakshminarayana| first=Raghava| title =PREMIERE: Jack Harlow \"Dark Knight\"| publisher =Mass Appeal| date =27 October 2017 | url =http://archive.massappeal.com/jack-harlow-dark-night-premiere/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Sub\">{{cite news | last=Shotwell| first=James| title =Jack Harlow's impending superstardom cannot be denied on \"Dark Knight\"| website =Substream| date =28 October 2017 | url =https://substreammagazine.com/2017/10/jack-harlow-dark-knight/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> The song would become the lead single off Harlow's mixtape ''Gazebo'', which was released in November 2017.<ref name=\"XXLBreak\"/> He went on a 14-city Gazebo Tour in support of the album. The Homies opened for Harlow, and the tour ended in January 2018.<ref name=\"LEOGaz\">{{cite news | last=Bishop| first=Syd| title =Jack Harlow talks about the songs on 'Gazebo'| newspaper =Louisville Eccentric Observer| date =24 January 2018 | url =https://www.leoweekly.com/2018/01/jack-harlow-talks/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"ISD\">{{cite news | last=Babcock| first=Trevor| title =Review: Jack Harlow makes a bold debut at the M-Shop| newspaper =Iowa State Daily| date =23 January 2018 | url =http://www.iowastatedaily.com/ames247/review-jack-harlow-makes-a-bold-debut-at-the-m/article_82206da8-00cb-11e8-a15d-5b165007912e.html| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> In May 2018, Harlow opened for indie rock band, [[Portugal. The Man]] on select tour dates.<ref name=\"Live\">{{cite news | last=Newcomb| first=Ming Lee| title =Portugal. The Man Announces New Tour Dates For 2018| publisher =Live for Live Music| date =6 February 2018 | url =https://liveforlivemusic.com/news/portugal-man-2018-new/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Times\">{{cite news | last=Tady| first=Scott| title =Portugal. The Man did it their way in Pittsburgh| newspaper =The Beaver County Times| date =23 May 2018 | url =http://www.timesonline.com/entertainmentlife/20180523/portugal-man-did-it-their-way-in-pittsburgh| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> The following month, he was featured alongside [[Lil James]] and Sixteen on the [[Skeme]] song \"Get Sumn\".<ref name=\"YC\">{{cite news | last=Garner| first=Matthew| title =Skeme \"Get Sumn\" feat. Jack Harlow, Sixteen & Lil James| publisher =Young California| date =11 June 2018 | url =http://www.youngcalifornia.com/2018/06/skeme-get-sumn-feat-jack-harlow-sixteen-lil-james/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2018, it was announced that Harlow had signed to [[DJ Drama]] and [[Don Cannon]]'s [[Atlantic Records]] imprint, Generation Now. He also released a video for his single \"Sundown\" on the day of the announcement.<ref name=\"BBAug\">{{cite news | last=Saponara| first=Michael| title =Jack Harlow Signs With Generation Now & Atlantic Records, Premieres Frenetic 'SUNDOWN' Video: Exclusive| publisher =Billboard| date =3 August 2018 | url =https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8468418/jack-harlow-signs-with-atlantic-records-generation-now-sundown-video| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"XXLGN\">{{cite news | last=Seabrook III| first=Robby| title =Jack Harlow Signs With Generation Now and Atlantic Records| publisher =XXL| date =3 August 2018 | url =http://www.xxlmag.com/video/2018/08/jack-harlow-signs-with-generation-now-atlantic-records/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> On August 17, Harlow released his major label debut mixtape, ''Loose''.<ref name=\"HotNew\">{{cite news | last=A.| first=Aron| title =Jack Harlow Drops New Project \"Loose\" Ft. CyHi The Prynce, K. Camp & More | website =HotNewHipHop| date =17 August 2018 | url =https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/jack-harlow-drops-new-project-loose-ft-cyhi-the-prynce-k-camp-and-more-new-mixtape.118343.html| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> The album featured guest verses from CyHi the Prynce, [[K Camp]], 2forwOyNE, and Taylor.<ref name=\"XXLLoose\">{{cite news | last=Mojica| first=Nick| title =Jack Harlow \"Loose\" Mixtape: Cyhi The Prynce and K Camp Deliver Guest Verses| publisher =XXL| date =17 August 2018 | url =http://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2018/08/jack-harlow-loose-mixtape/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> In September 2018, he performed at the [[Genius (website)|Genius]] IQ/BBQ event.<ref name=\"Vibe\">{{cite news | last=Arevalo| first=Lydia| title =2 Chainz To Headline Second Annual Genius IQ/BBQ| publisher =Vibe| date =24 August 2018 | url =https://www.vibe.com/2018/08/2-chainz-to-headline-second-annual-genius-bbq/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> In November 2018, Harlow embarked on a North American tour in support of ''Loose'' that is scheduled to end in late December.<ref name=\"DJB2018\">{{cite news | last=Chesman| first=Donna-Claire| title =How Jack Harlow Became a \"Somebody\" Onstage| publisher =DJ Booth| date =20 November 2018 | url =https://djbooth.net/features/2018-11-20-jack-harlow-became-somebody| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Loyola\">{{cite news | last=Demetrius| first=Alanna| title =Jack Harlow Puts on a Captivating Show at Reggies Rock Club| newspaper =Loyola Phoenix| date =13 November 2018 | url =http://loyolaphoenix.com/2018/11/jack-harlow-puts-on-a-captivating-show-at-reggies-rock-club/| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"BWW\">{{cite news | last=| first=| title =Jack Harlow Announces Fall Tour THE LOOSE TOUR| work =Broadway World| date =11 October 2018 | url =https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Jack-Harlow-Announces-Fall-Tour-THE-LOOSE-TOUR-20181011| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> That month, he also released a music video for the song, \"PickYourPhoneUp\", featuring K Camp.<ref name=\"Complex\">{{cite news | last=Diaz| first=Angel| title =Premiere: Jack Harlow and K.Camp Want You to \"PICKYOURPHONEUP\" In New Video| work =Complex| date =19 November 2018 | url =https://www.complex.com/music/2018/11/jack-harlow-new-video-premiere-pickyourphoneup-k-camp| accessdate =13 December 2018}}</ref> On August 21, 2019, Harlow released the single \"Thru the Night\" featuring [[Bryson Tiller]] and launched his US tour, which started in October of the same year.\n\nIn January 2020, he released \"Whats Poppin\", with a music video from video director [[Cole Bennett]], who had also directed videos for artists such as [[Juice Wrld]], [[Lil Tecca]], [[Lil Skies]], and [[Blueface]]. The music video, featuring a popular YouTube creator who goes by the name of \"Rhino\" from the channel called Loveliveserve, has surpassed twenty six million views as of March 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8548634/jack-harlow-whats-poppin-video|title=Jack Harlow Bounces Around the Diner in Cole Bennett-Directed 'Whats Poppin' Video: Watch|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/jack-harlow-snaps-on-braggadocios-banger-whats-poppin-new-song.1985876.html|title=Jack Harlow Snaps On Braggadocios Banger \"What's Poppin'\"|website=HotNewHipHop|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Jack Harlow - WHATS POPPIN (Dir. by @_ColeBennett_)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w9uWPBDHEKE|language=en|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> On his most recent birthday, March 13, 2020, he released a seven-track project called ''Sweet Action''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/03/jack-harlow-ep-sweet-action|title=Listen to Jack Harlow's EP 'Sweet Action'|work=Complex|date=March 14, 2020|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Mixtapes===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ List of mixtapes with selected album details\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em\"| Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Finally Handsome''\n|\n* Released: November 7, 2014\n* Label: [[Independent music|Self-released]]\n* Formats: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''18''\n|\n* Released: June 17, 2016\n* Label: Self-released\n* Formats: Digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Gazebo''\n|\n* Released: November 17, 2017\n* Label: Self-released\n* Formats: Digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Loose''\n|\n* Released: August 17, 2018\n* Label: Generation Now, [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n* Formats: Digital download\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Confetti''\n|\n* Released: September 20, 2019\n* Label: Generation Now, Atlantic\n* Format: Digital download\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ List of extended plays with selected details\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2