;\"|6<ref name=\"billboard1\"/>\n|-\n|US Rock Albums Chart\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|27<ref name=\"billboard1\"/>\n|-\n!Chart (2013)\n!Position\n|-\n|US Folk Albums Chart\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|47<ref>http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2013/folk-albums?page=4</ref>\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Single\n! Peak positions\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! style=\"width:65px;\"| [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]\n|-\n| 2011\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Barton Hollow\"<sup>A</sup>\n| 101\n|}\n*<sup>A</sup>Did not enter the Hot 100 but charted on [[Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Bubbling Under Hot 100 Week of March 3, 2012|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/charts/chart-search-results/singles/14065477|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=September 13, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top }}\n{{certification Table Entry|region=Canada|type=album|title=Barton Hollow|artist=The Civil Wars|award=Gold|access-date=August 10, 2014|relyear=2011}}\n{{certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|type=album|title=Barton Hollow|artist=The Civil Wars|award=Gold|certyear=2015|relyear=2011}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|type=album|title=Barton Hollow|artist=The Civil Wars|award=Gold|salesamount=623,000|salesref=<ref name=yahoo/>}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{The Civil Wars}}\n\n[[Category:2011 albums]]\n[[Category:The Civil Wars albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Charlie Peacock]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the Civil Wars album|the album's title track|Barton Hollow (song)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Barton Hollow\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[The Civil Wars]]\n| cover      = The Civil Wars - Barton Hollow.png\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2011|2|1|mf=yes}}\n| recorded   = The Art House, [[Nashville, Tennessee]]\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Folk rock]], [[alternative country]], [[indie folk]]\n| length     = {{Duration|m=46|s=27}}\n| label      = sensibility\n| producer   = [[Charlie Peacock]]\n| prev_title = [[Poison & Wine]]\n| prev_year  = 2009\n| next_title = [[The Civil Wars (album)|The Civil Wars]]\n| next_year  = 2013\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Barton Hollow\n | type        = Studio\n | single1     = [[Barton Hollow (song)|Barton Hollow]]\n | single1date = January 10, 2011\n}}\n}}\n'''''Barton Hollow''''' <ref>{{cite web|title=Barton Hollow|url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/product/B006VP1ONK?ie=UTF8&camp=1634&creativeASIN=B006VP1ONK&linkCode=xm2|publisher=Amazon.co.uk|accessdate=October 16, 2012}}</ref> is the first full-length studio album from [[The Civil Wars]]. Produced by [[Charlie Peacock]], it was released on February 1, 2011. It peaked at No.&nbsp;1 on the ''Billboard'' Digital Albums chart, No.&nbsp;10 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], No.&nbsp;1 on the ''Billboard'' Folk Albums chart, and No.&nbsp;2 on the ''Billboard'' Rock Albums chart, selling 25,000 copies in its first week.<ref>Billboard. Retrieved May 11, 2012 by [http://billboard.com/charts/billboard-200#/album/the-civil-wars/barton-hollow/1474607 Billboard.biz]</ref>  {{As of|2013|August}}, the album has sold 623,000 copies in the US.<ref name=yahoo>{{cite news|title=Week Ending Aug. 11, 2013. Albums: The Civil Wars, On Hiatus And On Top |url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/week-ending-aug-11-2013-albums-civil-wars-145540604.html |last=Grein |first=Paul |work=Chart Watch |publisher=Yahoo |date=August 14, 2013 |accessdate=August 24, 2013}}</ref>\n\nBarton Hollow was preceded by the lead single and title track, which was performed live on ''[[The Tonight Show with Jay Leno]]'' on January 14, 2011.<ref>[http://theaudioperv.com/2011/01/14/the-civil-wars-barton-hollow-113-leno/ The Audio Perv.] Retrieved May 11, 2012</ref>  A track on this album, \"Poison and Wine\" was previously released as a single from their EP ''[[Poison & Wine]]'' in 2009. On November 30, 2011, ''Barton Hollow'' was nominated for Grammys in the [[Grammy Award for Best Folk Album|Best Folk Album]] and [[Grammy Award for Best Country Duo/Group Performance|Best Country Duo/Group Performance]] categories, the latter for the title song. The album ended up winning both awards. Numerous publications noted that The Civil Wars were snubbed a Best New Artist nomination by [[The Grammys]]. At the ceremony The Civil Wars performed a portion of \"[[Barton Hollow (song)|Barton Hollow]]\".<ref>Roberts, Randall (November 30, 2011) Grammy Awards? Your Granny's Awards. Retrieved 2011-12-2, from [http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2011/11/critics-notebook-your-grannys-awards.html LATimes.com]</ref><ref>Maerz, Melissa (December 1, 2011) Grammys: Who Got Snubbed? Retrieved 2011-12-2, from [http://music-mix.ew.com/2011/12/01/grammys-snubs-nominees EW.com]</ref><ref>Christman, Ed (December 1, 2011) Retailers Predict Grammy Sales Bumps. Retrieved 2011-12-2, from [http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/retail/adele-bruno-mars-skrillex-retailers-project-1005601552.story Billboard.biz]</ref> The vinyl LP version of the record was pressed at [[United Record Pressing]] in Nashville, TN.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.10150570730304775.403926.45121499774&type=3 |title=Civil Wars - Barton Hollow (Sensibility Music) |publisher=Facebook |date= |accessdate=August 24, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album reviews\n| rev1 = Allmusic\n| rev1Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=allm/>\n| rev2 = MusicOMH\n| rev2Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=momh/>\t\n}}\n''Barton Hollow'' was included on the 2011 Best Album lists of [[NPR Music]],<ref>NPR Music: 50 Favorite Albums of 2011 (December 3, 2011) Retrieved 2011-12-5, from [http://npr.org/2011/12/05/142860882/50-favorites-b-e NPR.org]</ref> ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste Magazine]]'',<ref>Jackson, Josh (November 29, 2011) Paste Magazine: The 50 Best Albums of 2011. Retrieved 2011-12-5, from [http://pastemagazine.com/blogs/lists/2011/11/the-50-best-albums-of-2011.html?p=4 PasteMagazine.com]</ref> ''[[American Songwriter]]'',<ref>(2011, November 29) American Songwriter's 50 Top Albums of 2011. Retrieved 2011-12-5, from [http://americansongwriter.com/2011/11/american-songwriters-top-50-albums-of-2011/3/ AmericanSongwriter.com]</ref> ''[[Rough Trade (shops)|Rough Trade]]'',<ref>(2011, November 29) Albums of the Year Top 100. Retrieved 2011-12-5, from [http://roughtrade.com/site/content.lasso?page=AOY_2011_page2.html RoughTrade.com] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111205030858/http://roughtrade.com/site/content.lasso?page=AOY_2011_page2.html |date=December 5, 2011 }}</ref> [[Amazon.com]],<ref>Amazon (December 3, 2011) The Best Albums of 2011. Retrieved 2011-12-7, from [https://www.amazon.com/gp/feature.html/?docId=1000757031 Amazon.com]</ref> ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'',<ref>Time (December 7, 2011) Top 10 Albums of 2011. Retrieved 2011-12-7, from [http://time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,2101344_2101364_2101591,00.html ''Time'']</ref> [[iTunes]],<ref>iTunes Rewind 2011 (December 8, 2011) Retrieved 2011-12-10, from [http://tw.itunes.com/jCf iTunes]</ref> ''[[The Huffington Post]]'',<ref>Chenfeld, Cliff (December 8, 2011) The Best Music of 2011. Retrieved 2011-12-10, from [http://huffingtonpost.com/cliff-chenfeld/the-best-music-of-2011_b_1134189.html The Huffington Post]</ref> [[Associated Press]],<ref>Moody, Nekessa Mumbi (December 20, 2011) Adele tops AP's list of Best Albums of 2011. Retrieved 2011-12-22, from [http://sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/n/a/2011/12/20/entertainment/e071732S71.DTL SFGate.com]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111221155939/http://sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=%2Fn%2Fa%2F2011%2F12%2F20%2F